HEADWORD: After-wit
<hw>Aft"er-wit`</hw> <pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Wisdom or
perception that comes after it can be of use.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>After-wit</xex> comes too late when the mischief is
done.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>L'Estrange.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

